Arguments.Name: -wrap-ttl
Arguments.Description: Wraps the response in a cubbyhole token with the requested TTL. The response is available via the 'vault unwrap' command. The TTL is specified as a numeric string with suffix like '30s' or '5m'. This can also be specified via the VAULT_WRAP_TTL environment variable

Arguments.Name: -format
Arguments.Description: Print the output in the given format. Valid formats are 'table', 'json', 'yaml', or 'pretty'. The default is table. This can also be specified via the VAULT_FORMAT environment variable
